Here are the description for each mode 
```
#!c++

      /// \brief Set the collide mode of the body.
      /// \param[in] _mode Collision Mode,
      /// this can be: [all|none|sensors|fixed|ghost]
      /// all: collides with everything
      /// none: collides with nothing
      /// sensors: collides with everything else but other sensors
      /// fixed: collides with everything else but other fixed
      /// ghost: collides with everything else but other ghost
      public: void SetCollideMode(const std::string &_mode);
```
A quick search for function usage finds 2 usages in MudPlugin and 2 usage in the integration tests. All of them set the mode to `all`    

![Screenshot from 2017-09-07 18-44-43.png](data/bitbucket.org/repo/ak8x4z/images/814142239-Screenshot_from_2017-09-07_18-44-43.png)   

I think the default value of the collision mode should be `all`, instead of empty stated in this PR. And I didn't see any hurt to include this change. 
@scpeters  What about your thoughts?
